1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,720
 So now that we've introduced CSRF conceptually,

2
00:00:02,720 --> 00:00:05,120
 let's talk about how we actually implement it

3
00:00:05,120 --> 00:00:06,200
 running in Django.

4
00:00:06,200 --> 00:00:10,720
 So if you remember, I didn't really point this out

5
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:11,900
 too much when we went through it.

6
00:00:11,900 --> 00:00:16,260
 This was my first form where I showed you how data

7
00:00:16,260 --> 00:00:19,600
 could be transported to the server using a POST request.

8
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:22,720
 If you look at the top, I have this little annotation

9
00:00:22,720 --> 00:00:25,840
 @csrf_exempt, and there's a little import above it

10
00:00:25,840 --> 00:00:29,980
 in the views file, and what I was basically telling Django

11
00:00:29,980 --> 00:00:34,720
 is don't blow this up because I'm not handling CSRF properly.

12
00:00:34,720 --> 00:00:38,720
 So what we're gonna do is we're gonna do the exact same view

13
00:00:38,720 --> 00:00:41,240
 except we're just not gonna have that little thing.

14
00:00:41,240 --> 00:00:43,240
 So we'll call this one fail form,

15
00:00:43,240 --> 00:00:46,360
 and we're gonna throw out a form,

16
00:00:46,360 --> 00:00:49,040
 we're gonna press submit, everything looks fine,

17
00:00:49,040 --> 00:00:53,900
 the only difference is I did not turn off CSRF processing.

18
00:00:53,900 --> 00:00:57,400
 So on a POST request, CSRF processing is on by default,

19
00:00:57,400 --> 00:01:00,140
 which means that we have to do something explicitly

20
00:01:00,140 --> 00:01:03,420
 when we're making POST forms, but I didn't do it yet,

21
00:01:03,420 --> 00:01:06,060
 so this is what happens if you don't do it.

22
00:01:06,060 --> 00:01:10,680
 So you get a form and you press the,

23
00:01:10,680 --> 00:01:13,040
 type some stuff in and you hit submit query,

24
00:01:13,040 --> 00:01:15,080
 and boom, you get this forbidden message.

25
00:01:15,080 --> 00:01:19,120
 That's a 403, so among all the HTTP responses,

26
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:21,160
 we've got 200, which is okay, we've got 302,

27
00:01:21,160 --> 00:01:24,460
 which is moved, and we've got 404, which is not found.

28
00:01:24,460 --> 00:01:26,760
 403 is you're not getting this page,

29
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:28,480
 but not because I don't have it,

30
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:30,780
 but because you're not authorized to do it.

31
00:01:30,780 --> 00:01:33,660
 So this is it aborting and stopping the POST,

32
00:01:33,660 --> 00:01:36,280
 so it comes in, it looked up the session,

33
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:39,620
 and everything looked good except the CSRF did not match.

34
00:01:39,620 --> 00:01:44,040
 Now, we are a legit server, so what we've gotta do

35
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:46,720
 is we've gotta actually add the CSRF

36
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:49,800
 to the POST on the way out, okay?

37
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:53,160
 So this is the exact same POST,

38
00:01:53,160 --> 00:01:55,400
 and I'm doing this kind of at a low level,

39
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:58,060
 and I'll show you a much easier way to do it in a minute.

40
00:01:58,060 --> 00:02:00,920
 So we have an input hidden, I just happen to know

41
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:04,920
 that CSRF middleware token is the proper name for it,

42
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:06,360
 and I'm just gonna have a placeholder,

43
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:08,320
 which is underscore underscore token,

44
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:10,560
 and so then what I'm gonna do is I'm gonna talk

45
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:13,280
 to that middleware, CSRF, get token.

46
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:15,000
 Now, that token is probably just a number

47
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:17,560
 sitting in the session, but I don't need to know that,

48
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:20,440
 I just say, hey, give me the token for the current request.

49
00:02:20,440 --> 00:02:22,780
 Request is, of course, all that data that's coming in,

50
00:02:22,780 --> 00:02:24,840
 it's got the session, it's got everything else in it.

51
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:28,120
 So hey, give me that token, this is a big, long string,

52
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:30,160
 which is really just a big, long, random number,

53
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:32,520
 a big, long, random string, and then what I'm gonna do

54
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:34,540
 is take whatever that big, long, random number is,

55
00:02:34,540 --> 00:02:36,600
 and I'm gonna replace this little bit with a stir,

56
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:39,800
 a simple replace, and then I'm gonna send that out.

57
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:44,800
 So this time, when we go to that page,

58
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:48,060
 you'll see that now we have an input type equals hidden,

59
00:02:48,060 --> 00:02:50,400
 name equals CSRF middleware token,

60
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:53,920
 and then the big, long middleware token, whatever that is,

61
00:02:53,920 --> 00:02:56,080
 and then now when we submit it,

62
00:02:56,080 --> 00:03:00,200
 it bundles up both the guess and the middleware token,

63
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:02,800
 and it actually bundles up the submit as well,

64
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:06,180
 if it's got a name, and sends that in as post data.

65
00:03:06,180 --> 00:03:08,160
 So now when it dumps out, you see,

66
00:03:08,160 --> 00:03:11,920
 oh, well, you got guess equals 42 and CSRF middleware.

67
00:03:11,920 --> 00:03:15,160
 Now, by the time it's got to this point,

68
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:16,720
 we're not really doing the checking here,

69
00:03:16,720 --> 00:03:19,360
 the checking was done before the view started.

70
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:21,240
 And so if we go back to the view here,

71
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:25,220
 the checking is done before it gets to here.

72
00:03:25,220 --> 00:03:29,280
 When you're dispatching from urls.py to this,

73
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:32,360
 and it says, hmm, you didn't tell me not to do CSRF,

74
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:35,000
 and it's not done properly, so I'm gonna blow you up.

75
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,160
 So if it's gonna work, it's already worked.

76
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:38,360
 The fact that we've come in here

77
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:40,600
 and we're dumping this stuff out of the post,

78
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:42,560
 that's just sort of like we see it,

79
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:44,760
 but it would have blown up before

80
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:47,000
 it would have even got to our code at that point.

81
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,160
 But we do get it and see it as post data.

82
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:52,320
 We don't need to because by the very fact

83
00:03:52,320 --> 00:03:55,720
 that our view is running means that the CSRF processing

84
00:03:55,720 --> 00:03:58,000
 has been successful, okay?

85
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:01,060
 And again, the rogue system has to somehow

86
00:04:01,060 --> 00:04:04,360
 get its hands on this, the actual number of the CSRF,

87
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:05,960
 and that changes every time you log in.

88
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:09,320
 And literally, it could change every hour or so or whatever.

89
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:11,200
 And so it's a hard number to guess

90
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:13,920
 and it's a hard number to get your hands on.

91
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:18,440
 Now, that manual thing is not the easiest way to put this in.

92
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:20,560
 There's an easy way in CSRF.

93
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:24,680
 You simply say, so here's our form, here's our slash form.

94
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:27,480
 I do all the stuff I wanna do that I wanna do

95
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:31,120
 and then I use the code, it is called template tag.

96
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:34,080
 When you have CSRF enabled in your Python,

97
00:04:34,080 --> 00:04:37,040
 you have a template tag of CSRF underscore token.

98
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:39,880
 And that emits the input, the type equals hidden,

99
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:41,680
 the write name, and all that stuff.

100
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:44,380
 So you, as the developer using templates,

101
00:04:44,380 --> 00:04:48,380
 you don't have to know anything about that, okay?

102
00:04:48,380 --> 00:04:51,480
 And so this, that's how we do CSRF.

103
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:53,380
 And the only other thing we got is guessing game

104
00:04:53,380 --> 00:04:55,840
 and then we're gonna pass a message into that

105
00:04:55,840 --> 00:04:58,080
 and we're gonna do that in a bit.

106
00:04:58,080 --> 00:05:00,740
 We're gonna use this for a whole bunch of little examples.

107
00:05:00,740 --> 00:05:04,520
 So kind of remember this particular guest.html template.

108
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:06,440
 But the key right now that we're talking about

109
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:09,220
 is the fact that we've got this CSRF token in.

110
00:05:09,220 --> 00:05:11,160
 Now, I'm gonna write a bunch of guessing games

111
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:12,040
 and these guessing games,

112
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:14,960
 I'm actually going to start checking the guesses.

113
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:16,460
 So I'm gonna have a function in this view

114
00:05:16,460 --> 00:05:18,240
 that's got called check guess.

115
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:19,160
 And it's pretty simple.

116
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:21,360
 It returns a string or false.

117
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:24,100
 If the guess is an actual non-false thing,

118
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:26,560
 we check to see if it's too low, too high,

119
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:27,960
 or right on time.

120
00:05:27,960 --> 00:05:32,380
 Or if it doesn't compute, if it doesn't convert,

121
00:05:32,380 --> 00:05:34,580
 if this guess throws a trace back,

122
00:05:34,580 --> 00:05:37,000
 well, then we'll say bad format equals guess

123
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,360
 and then just because it probably came from the user,

124
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:41,220
 we're gonna escape it and then send that back.

125
00:05:41,220 --> 00:05:42,480
 So whatever it does,

126
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:45,960
 we're gonna send back a nice little message going back.

127
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:49,920
 And so here is a simple guessing game

128
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:51,520
 that we're going to do.

129
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:56,520
 And so we're using a class-based view this time.

130
00:05:56,520 --> 00:06:00,640
 Of course, we extend the class view.

131
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:03,480
 And remember how it works is it's not just a function.

132
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:04,560
 We actually have two methods.

133
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:05,720
 One is a get request.

134
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:09,180
 And the get is called when we're receiving get request.

135
00:06:09,180 --> 00:06:12,280
 And the post is called when we're receiving a post request.

136
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:15,500
 This alone is one of the nice reasons to do this.

137
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:18,920
 You don't actually have to say, if it's a get do one thing,

138
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:20,120
 if it's a post do another thing.

139
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:21,560
 We just have two methods.

140
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:25,360
 And Django properly routes the requests in.

141
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:28,200
 And so this is gonna be a form post.

142
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:32,960
 So on the get, we just render with no messages.

143
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:34,680
 We render with no messages.

144
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:38,060
 And we have a CSRF token that goes out,

145
00:06:38,060 --> 00:06:39,800
 so we just render it.

146
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:42,600
 Then we'll click the button so that this render right here

147
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:43,720
 will produce this page.

148
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:47,560
 Then we type in the guess of 42 and we hit submit query.

149
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:50,960
 And then that bundles it all up including CSRF

150
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:52,240
 and goes to the post.

151
00:06:52,240 --> 00:06:56,380
 Now the CSRF, as long as we put it in that template,

152
00:06:56,380 --> 00:06:58,900
 we don't have to care because before that post method

153
00:06:58,900 --> 00:07:01,520
 gets activated, CSRF has been processed.

154
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:04,320
 And we get a 403 if the CSRF isn't right.

155
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:08,880
 So if we go back up here, you don't put this in,

156
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:12,240
 and you run this code, the CSRF token, you don't put it in,

157
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:15,920
 then it's never gonna make it to the post.

158
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:19,000
 I mean, it blows up in route to the post

159
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,820
 if the CSRF doesn't happen.

160
00:07:20,820 --> 00:07:23,040
 But we've got CSRF and it's all automatic.

161
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:25,420
 We just throw that one line inside of our form

162
00:07:25,420 --> 00:07:27,040
 and that's all we've gotta do.

163
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:31,400
 So we put 42 in, we hit submit query,

164
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:33,540
 pass the CSRF, it comes in.

165
00:07:33,540 --> 00:07:36,940
 So we grab the post data, the guess from the post data.

166
00:07:36,940 --> 00:07:38,760
 We call my little check message,

167
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:40,920
 check guess that's gonna give me that little message,

168
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:42,680
 whether it's too low, too high,

169
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:44,440
 or some kind of other mistake.

170
00:07:44,440 --> 00:07:46,600
 And then I'm gonna pass in a context,

171
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:49,840
 the string message has that string.

172
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:52,160
 And if then we go, do I have it down here?

173
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:53,840
 No, have it up here.

174
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:55,140
 So then the message comes out.

175
00:07:55,140 --> 00:07:57,840
 So this, you'll notice I've surrounded this by an if,

176
00:07:57,840 --> 00:08:00,400
 so the message is false or not present,

177
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:01,880
 then it doesn't put anything out.

178
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:04,280
 But if it is, it actually puts the message out.

179
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:08,560
 And so out comes the guess.

180
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:10,680
 And so this is what it looks like

181
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:13,840
 when we do a get request, we see this,

182
00:08:13,840 --> 00:08:16,840
 then we're gonna see all this stuff,

183
00:08:16,840 --> 00:08:19,240
 we're gonna type our number in, we're gonna hit submit query,

184
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:22,200
 and then it's gonna fire up a post request.

185
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:24,820
 And so then it's gonna come back into the post request,

186
00:08:24,820 --> 00:08:27,740
 it's gonna get the guess from the post data,

187
00:08:27,740 --> 00:08:29,080
 it's gonna check it,

188
00:08:29,080 --> 00:08:31,160
 and then it's gonna pass the message in,

189
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:33,520
 and so the message is gonna come out here,

190
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:38,280
 and then we're gonna return that page.

191
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:41,920
 And so you're gonna see something like congratulations 42.

192
00:08:41,920 --> 00:08:44,360
 So that took, that was part of the post.

193
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:49,240
 And so we now have made a successful guessing game.

194
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:51,100
 So next we're gonna talk about,

195
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:53,640
 just when we get something working,

196
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:56,240
 there's always something that we have to say,

197
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:59,480
 oh, but there's a little detail that we forgot about.

198
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:03,320
 So up next, we'll talk about post and refresh,

199
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:06,360
 which is a little problem that we're just gonna have to fix.

